d power structures. Such public spectacles of violence also force members of the community to choose sides—openly show support for the goals of the violence, or risk becoming victims, themselves. Tracing the ways in which public displays of violence unfold, Show Time reveals how the perpetrators exploit the fluidity of social ties for their own ends.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGenocidexSocial aspectszRwandaxHistoryy20th century. 0aLynchingxSocial aspectszMarylandxHistoryy20th century. 0aMassacresxSocial aspectszBosnia and HerzegovinaxHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitical violencexSocial aspectszBosnia and HerzegovinaxHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitical violencexSocial aspectszRwandaxHistoryy20th century. 0aViolencexPsychological aspectsxHistoryy20th century. 0aViolencexSocial aspectsxHistoryy20th century. 4aHumanities & Human Rights. 4aInternational Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Violence in Society.2bisacsh  aordinary perpetrators of violence, lynching, ethnic violence, ethnic cleansing, sud bosne i hercegovine,.1 aFinnemore, Martha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFinnemore, Martha, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWood, Elisabeth Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073908408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-